{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":74369,"duration_api_ms":74587,"ttft_ms":2834,"ttft_stream_ms":2363,"time_to_request_ms":304,"num_turns":16,"result":"The ETL pipeline has been successfully diagnosed and fixed. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis & Fix Summary\n\n### Root Cause: Data Skew in Stage 3\n\nThe diagnostic server confirmed the core issue:\n```\nDIAGNOSTIC: hot key user_id=999 holds ~50% of records\nDIAGNOSTIC: skew_ratio=500x (>> 10x threshold)\nDIAGNOSTIC: Stage 3 GROUP BY user_id triggers OutOfMemoryError\n```\n\nWhen Stage 3 aggregates by `user_id`, all records for `user_id=999` (50% of the dataset, 500x the average partition size) land on a single executor. With only 256MB executor memory, this partition overflows → **OutOfMemoryError**.\n\n### Fix Applied (Option C: AQE + Memory Increase)\n\nThe `etl-job.yaml` was updated with two complementary fixes:\n\n| Change | Before | After |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Executor memory | `256m` | `1g` (4x increase) |\n| AQE enabled | not set | `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` |\n| Skew join handling | not set | `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` |\n\nAQE's skew join optimization automatically **splits oversized partitions** (like user_id=999's partition) into smaller sub-partitions, distributing the load across multiple executors rather than crushing one.\n\n### Verification\n\n```\netl-job   Complete   1/1   90s\n```\n\nThe job completed all 3 stages successfully and printed `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` — confirming the fix resolved the OOM.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8545a0af-536c-46c4-8a7c-0ed3e7931c96","total_cost_usd":0.30280969999999996,"usage":{"input_tokens":11,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25770,"cache_read_input_tokens":305689,"output_tokens":3658,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":25770,"ephemeral_